# text mode
- Allows you to write ascii to video memory
- 16 inque colors
- Write chartacters to screen without setting individual pixels

# Writing to video memory
- Starts at address 0xB8000 for colored displays
- Monochrome isplays start as 0xB0000
- Each character takes up two bytes
 - byte zero is ascii character
 - byte one is the color code
- Write black "A" to column 0 row 0
 - 0xb8000 = 'A'
 - 0xb8001 = 0x00 (code for black)
